status.description: This issue has been validated/reproduced, but has not been prioritized yet.
status.name: Confirmed

fields.description:
I noticed that when using Windows10/Firefox, deleting large buckets takes forever or freezes when deleting.  I tried to delete a bucket that had over 1000 objects.  When the deletion starts, it gets to 100 objects, then stops.  I waited for about 5 mins or so, the progress appeared to stop so I cancelled and started again.  I saw 100 objects get deleted and then the progress stopped.  I cancelled and started again.  This behavior repeated until all were deleted.  If I try the same experiment using Edge or Chrome on linux, the bucket gets deleted without issues.   I see this in the logs when it attempts to delete.
